We can begin our solution by expressing $10x^2 + 12xy + 10y^2$ in terms of $x$ and $y$. Recognize that:  $$3x + y = 10\quad\Rightarrow\quad y=10-3x.$$Substituting into $10x^2 + 12xy + 10y^2$, we have:  \begin{align*}
10x^2 + 12xy + 10y^2 &= 10x^2 + 12x(10-3x) + 10(10-3x)^2\\
&= 10x^2 + 120x-36x^2 + 100(10-3x)^2\\
&=10x^2 + 120x+100(100-60x+9x^2)\\
&=\boxed{900}.
\end{align*}
